        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 12 at 3:06PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 305 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Madison, moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Madison, Capshaw, Toney, Harvest, and Huntsville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
